The paper proposes a novel ensemble clustering approach that focuses on evaluating the reliability of clusters and exploiting local diversity in the ensemble to enhance consensus performance. This involves using an entropic criterion to estimate the uncertainty of each cluster, introducing a novel ensemble-driven cluster validity measure, and presenting a locally weighted co-association matrix. These techniques are relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), data mining (cs.DM), and computer vision (cs.CV).
